Let me analyze the images and provide a detailed solution:

Main Target Image Analysis:
- Structure is 3 layers high
- Red arch/curved blocks form the bottom and top layers
- A yellow rectangular block connects the layers in the middle
- Total of 5 blocks used (3 red, 2 yellow)

Block Dictionary Selection:
- Red curved blocks: Indices 1, 2, 5, 6
- Yellow rectangular block: Indices 9, 10, 13, 14

Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1 (bottom left red arch)
    Step2: Move block with index 5 (bottom right red arch)
    Step3: Move block with index 9 (yellow rectangular block connecting bottom layer)
    Step4: Move block with index 2 (top left red arch)
    Step5: Move block with index 6 (top right red arch)
    Step6: Move block with index 13 (yellow rectangular block connecting top layer)
}

This sequence will recreate the target structure exactly, using blocks from the dictionary without any rotation.
